&lt;div&gt;The T/VBR level 1 is defined by percentage of time or values of glucose of 3.0 mmol/L - 3.8 mmol/ L.&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div&gt;These are represented by the proportion of values below range (VBR) and/ or percentage time below range (TBR). These are determined from capillary blood (fingerstick testing) and interstitial glucose (continuous glucose monitoring device) readings respectively.&lt;/div&gt;
                                &lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;
